⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Metroids
node MET · MET · ⟦The Metroids:MET:cf029f⟧

WHO   — The Metroids — the bio-weapon
WHAT  — Jellyfish-like energy-drainers that latch onto living prey and siphon its life-force away — weightless, eerie, and lethal, frozen and shattered only by the cold of the Ice Beam.
WHERE — MET · Metroid  Framework inputs: Metroid (1986) & Super Metroid (1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because they were made to be a weapon — life that ends life; and because in the wrong hands a single colony of them would drain the galaxy dry, which is why Samus is sent into the dark to end them.
HOW   — By drifting upon their prey on weightless air, fastening to it, and pulling the very energy of life out of it — multiplying in the depths of Zebes until only the cold of the Ice Beam can freeze and shatter them.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  We are the hunger that floats — touch us and your life pours out; only the cold can break us.

